ect resolved value.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.86,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":8,"description":"When a referenced cell's value changes, all dependent formulas are recalculated in the correct topological order.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Behavior is explicitly about orchestration/state handoff across dependency graph and recalculation engine; this is beyond isolated function logic (MOCK-MISS). No requirement for real OS/network/subprocess, so System is disqualified. No AI/ML decisions, so Agentic/Workflow are disqualified.","test_description":"Create dependency chain/diamond in an in-memory workbook, evaluate once, mutate a source cell, trigger recalculation, and assert each dependent cell matches expected post-update values consistent with topological recompute semantics.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.9,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":9,"description":"The undo operation after editing a formula restores both the formula text and all previously computed dependent values.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure appears at interaction boundary among edit command handling, undo stack state, and recalculation/dependency propagation. Unit tests on undo stack alone can miss dependent-value restoration bugs. No real infrastructure requirement in behavior text, and no AI dependence; thus not System/Agentic/Workflow.","test_description":"In-memory workbook with dependent formulas: evaluate baseline, edit an upstream formula, confirm changed dependents, perform undo via public API, assert restored formula text and restored dependent computed values.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.9,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":10,"description"